No expense spared - Fully Customized
Taken to the range only for testing and customization
Aimpoint sight shown is not included
Adams Arms Gas Piston Driven Upper
- Gas piston operation prevents corrosive byproducts from entering the receiver. This is a valuable feature when using surplus 5.45x39
- Melonite Finish further prevents corrosion
-Ion-Bonded Bolt Carrier Group
- further prevents corrosion
Read more about this upper here: http://www.adamsarms.net/5-45x39-16-carbine-base-upper
Custom shaved Hammer for Lighter Trigger Pull (Heavy spring also included)

5.45x39 surplus ammo generally requires a stiffer spring in order to sufficiently strike the primer. This results in a heavier trigger pull. In order to avoid this, I shaved down the hammer, lowering its weight and thus increasing its velocity. This results in a successful primer strike 100% of the time, without the heavier trigger pull. A heavier spring is also provided, should you prefer that option.

876,http://www.armslist.com/posts/3534876,For Sale:  Hi Point 9mm carbine - loaded with extras,"metro, Minneapolis / St. Paul, Minnesota",$ 375,"Listed On: Wednesday, September 24, 2014",Rifles,Hi Point                                                                                ,9mm Luger (9x19)                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"For the record, this is a carbine, but I didn't see that as an option for listing.

It's in perfect shape with less than 400 rounds fired (I think only 340 but I'm not positive), but round count shouldn't even matter because of the manufacturer's unconditional no questions asked lifetime warranty, every single part is guaranteed for life!

It's about as loaded as these can be (and still be practical) with a multi-colored laser dot scope, tactical light, flash suppressor, 3 position folding front grip (with a multi-tool inside for field stripping and cleaning), 4 magazines, a brand new padded sling, a carry case and I'm even throwing in a bore snake for easier cleaning.

It's one of the funnest guns you'll ever shoot. The 16.5"" barrel shoots regular ole 9mm FMJ 115 grain target loads up to over 1,500 feet per second with 575 foot pounds of energy, yet there's virtually no recoil with this gun (it's like shooting a .22 rifle) letting you have follow up shots as fast as you can squeeze the trigger AND actually still hit the bullseye each and every time! But it's not just a fun gun, you could easily load this with some real nice +P or even +P+ hollow points and have a very nice home defense or truck gun that pretty much the whole family could use (regardless of their height or strength) because of how user friendly and easy to use this carbine really is.

Like I stated, I've fired less than 400 rounds through it, all were flawless and I clean every one of my firearms after each range trip. 250 or so rounds were various FMJ's playing around with different speeds and weights for fun and 100 were 115 grain JHP's that I carry in my handgun (same caliber keeps things simple in a SHTF scenario) ... the ballistics gel reacted as if I had fired hot .357's out of my 6"" barrel S&W; I was very surprised and impressed with the permanent cavity and the penetration! Unless you live in bear country, this will easily stop whatever threat you or your loved ones might face in your home.

I would keep this carbine forever, but I'm moving to Spain and then Germany (for work) for at least 4 years and perhaps even longer, so I'm selling my firearms instead of going through all the hassle of trying to ship them over and get them registered when I'll still be a US citizen.

I'm not interested in any trades right now because we're selling just about everything we own (easier than shipping or storing for several years) and any new stuff I'd get, we'd just have to figure out how to ship or store that as well.
I'm also willing to sell 600 rounds of 9mm FMJ's for an extra $150.00 to the buyer if you want some affordable ammo.
Thanks for looking!
BTW - we're not moving until December, so I'd appreciate not getting any low ball offers on what is already a great price - thanks."
